@startuml frontend-observability-trace-walkthrough
title Single-trace walkthrough — admin clicks "Update Provider"
autonumber
skinparam backgroundColor #0f172a
skinparam defaultFontColor #e2e8f0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #94a3b8
skinparam ArrowFontColor #cbd5e1
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #1e293b
skinparam noteBorderColor #475569
skinparam noteFontColor #e2e8f0
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #1e3a8a
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #3b82f6
skinparam sequenceParticipantFontColor #e2e8f0
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #1e293b
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #475569

actor "User\n(browser)" as U
participant "SettingsService\n(admin-fe)" as SS
participant "ActivityLogger\ntrace<T>()" as AL
participant "tracingInterceptor" as TI
participant "Faro Web SDK" as Faro
participant "Alloy\n(192.168.1.160)" as Alloy
participant "OTel Collector" as OC
participant "Gateway\n(YARP)" as GW
participant "ai-service-v2" as AI

note over U, Faro
  Browser-side: one TraceId is created here
  and flows through every component below.
end note

U -> SS : click "Save Provider"
SS -> AL : updateProvider(req).pipe(logger.trace('ai provider update'))
AL -> Faro : tracer.startSpan('activity ai provider update')
note right of AL: TraceId = abc123\nSpanId = act01
AL -> AL : context.with(setSpan, () => source.subscribe(...))

note over AL, TI
  Inside the active context:
  tracingInterceptor creates the HTTP span
  as a CHILD of the activity span
  → same TraceId, parent = act01.
end note

AL -> TI : HTTP PUT /ai/v2/Settings/update-provider
TI -> Faro : tracer.startSpan('HTTP PUT /...')
note right of TI: parent = act01\nSpanId = http02
TI -> GW : traceparent: 00-abc123-http02-01

GW -> AI : proxy with traceparent\n(parent context propagated)
AI -> AI : UpdateProviderCommand pipeline
note right of AI: Serilog logs auto-enriched\nwith TraceId = abc123
AI --> GW : 200 OK
GW --> TI : 200

TI -> Faro : HTTP span ends (duration recorded)
AL -> Faro : pushLog('[admin] ai provider update ok',\n  level=info, elapsedMs=110, model=gpt-4.1,\n  spanContext={traceId: abc123, spanId: act01})
AL -> Faro : span.end() (activity span)

note over Faro
  Faro batches logs + spans
  and POSTs to Alloy.
end note

Faro -> Alloy : POST faro.elkhair.tech/collect
Alloy -> OC : OTLP traces (direct)\nOTLP logs (via Loki bridge)

note over OC
  parse_fe_body: extract logfmt fields
  filter/fe_log_only: drop measurements
  fe_service_name: ApplicationName=admin-fe
  promote_trace_ids: hex TraceId in attrs
  set_es_mapping_mode: raw
end note

OC -> OC : fan-out → Jaeger + Seq + spanmetrics + Elasticsearch

note over U, AI
  Result in Grafana "Find by Trace Id"
  with TraceId = abc123:
  • 2 FE spans (activity + HTTP) from admin-fe
  • N backend logs from gateway and ai-service-v2
  • 1 FE log line "[admin] ai provider update ok"
  • All correlated, all clickable to Jaeger
end note

@enduml
